text: ‚Äúwelcome, peanut‚Äù

How are people feeling about announcements?

1. When they first launched, a bunch of complaints about them being too spammy. 

2. Another population of people claim they never check the channels tab.

If we were to move announcements into the All / Priority tab (vs. keeping them in Channels), how would you feel?

Saw a few casts grumbling about the next iteration of frames

Clearing up misconceptions:

1. We circulated earlier versions of the public draft with a dozen or teams who are actively building frames.

2. Existing frames will continue to work as is. If people continue to build them and they have meaningful usage, we will support them.

3. Our goal with the changes is to give developers *more* surface area to build better experiences and *more* reliability for one shot actions like transactions (still clunky today).

4. Frames are just links. So other clients can choose to adopt or not and they will start work.

5. Frames are Farcaster primitives not just Warpcast because they contain social context, e.g. a user‚Äôs FID

Looking for 5 developers to prototype App Frames with us next week. 

We'll help with heavy lifting on design, integration and support. If you're interested, please reply with your current frame. 

https://warpcast.notion.site/App-Frames-Public-12a6a6c0c101805f84f0ca8bb27047d6

text:
Day 19 of my zero following experiment. 

1. It‚Äôs really hard to keep up with what‚Äôs going on inside of Farcaster. I forgot how much I depend on my network to keep me in the loop. But the main reason I did this was that I wasn‚Äôt seeing enough of the people I wanted to see. I had to rely on setting notifications for them and even that didn‚Äôt always work. Now I stalk about 15 peoples profiles daily and use group chats heavily. 


2. My home feed is weird. For a while it struggled but now it mostly shows me very engaged posts in channels I follow. This is AWESOME. I don‚Äôt want to trending feed button. I want a ‚Äútrending in the channels you follow‚Äù button. This is way more likely to lead to content discovery. I see so much from these channels that I wouldn‚Äôt organically see because I don‚Äôt follow most of the folks who were posting there. My feed is full of /yellow and /superrare and /nature photos and art and I love it. Show me the best of each channel so I can find cool people.

pure memecoins are a pyramid scheme that will collapse as soon as 

A) the same people keep winning (as this means the average person is losing $ consistently)

and

B) new buyers entering the system are exhausted (there's a limited amount).

A is already happening (KOLs are driving token prices top down) & not sure how much of B is left.

History rhymes - exact same thing happened with NFTs.

Memecoins are less of a serious thing if you look at them like prediction markets. 

Sell = bet No 
Buy = bet Yes 
Every memecoin will end (collapse)

Unfortunately, I don't think most retail users see it this way, and they will get burned. Probably an opportunity for a safer more transparent experience.
